theorem Topology.dense_and_P1_implies_denseInterior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) → Topology.P1 (X:=X) A → Dense (interior (A : Set X)) := by
  intro hDense hP1
  -- `P1` gives equality of the two closures.
  have h_eq : closure (A : Set X) = closure (interior (A : Set X)) :=
    (Topology.P1_iff_closure_eq_closureInterior (X := X) (A := A)).1 hP1
  -- Since `A` is dense, its closure is the whole space.
  have h_clA : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
  -- Hence the closure of `interior A` is also the whole space.
  have h_clInt : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    calc
      closure (interior (A : Set X)) = closure (A : Set X) := by
        simpa using h_eq.symm
      _ = (Set.univ : Set X) := h_clA
  -- Conclude that `interior A` is dense.
  simpa [Dense] using h_clInt

theorem Topology.interior_interior_interior_eq_interior {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (interior (interior (A : Set X))) = interior A := by
  simp [interior_interior]
